{"id": "EUVD-2022-55574", "enisaUuid": "f3f57421-0ba9-3fd8-a596-da4055b849f4", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nMIPS: SGI-IP27: Fix platform-device leak in bridge_platform_create()\n\nIn error case in bridge_platform_create after calling\nplatform_device_add()/platform_device_add_data()/\nplatform_device_add_resources(), release the failed\n'pdev' or it will be leak, call platform_device_put()\nto fix this problem.\n\nBesides, 'pdev' is divided into 'pdev_wd' and 'pdev_bd',\nuse platform_device_unregister() to release sgi_w1\nresources when xtalk-bridge registration fails.", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:25", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-04T21:31:01", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/da2aecef866b476438d02c662507a0e4e818da9d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/93296e7ab774230b7c36541dead10b6da39b650f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d7ac29e60d0ff71e9e414af595b8c92800f7fa90", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/48025893b3e31b917ad654d28d23fff66681cac4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/11bec9cba4de06b3c0e9e4041453c2caaa1cbec1", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50281"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50281"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0dec6c3a-0004-3371-9a62-a91e173c2b8f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5dc76a96e95ae041c1d8e52714bd77576b35919b <48025893b3e31b917ad654d28d23fff66681cac4"}, {"id": "157acfeb-2a3e-324d-859a-7a8b332d368f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.17"}, {"id": "24e309a9-a5d9-3bca-8d21-f0e129ec1199", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.5"}, {"id": "531e4a02-b7e1-3b60-b9b1-2c609e838d6e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "61cb6279-dfe4-3e60-814f-8b673f2fb265", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5dc76a96e95ae041c1d8e52714bd77576b35919b <da2aecef866b476438d02c662507a0e4e818da9d"}, {"id": "8019d8f4-bd19-362c-9fa3-72e55bf66d